Preheat #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a large #pot{} of salted water.

Coat the bottom of a deep #baking tray{} with @oil{}. Pop into the oven.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{3} into 4cm chunks.

Boil potatoes until edges are soft, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{}. Sprinkle on 1 tbsp @flour{1%tbsp} and shake to fluff up. Carefully add to the baking tray. Turn to coat in the oil. Season with @salt{}. Roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{2} and halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the carrots onto one side of a large (lined) baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried thyme{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, turning halfway, ~{25-30%minutes}.

In a #bowl{}, mix together 1 tbsp @butter{1%tbsp}, garlic, @dried oregano{1%sachet}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Use the back of a #spoon{} to spread the herby butter over the @Irish turkey breast{1}.

Lay the turkey onto the other side of the baking tray with the carrots.

Pop back in the oven and roast until turkey is cooked through, ~{20-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw turkey and its packaging. Turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Brussels sprouts{250%grams} and halve through the root.

When the potatoes have 10 mins left to cook, place a #pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Fry sprouts and @Irish bacon lardons{100%grams} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add a splash of @water{} and cover.

Cook until sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

> TIP: If you like, use the waiting time to do some washing up.

Place a pot over high heat with two-thirds of the @cranberry chutney{3%sachets} and @butter{2%tbsp}. Bring to the boil.

Add a splash of @water{} to loosen if required. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the sprouts and bacon are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Stir in the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} and @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly.

When the carrots are cooked, drizzle over the @honey{2%sachets} and toss to coat.

Share the herby turkey between plates.

Serve the honeyed carrots, balsamic Brussels sprouts and roast potatoes alongside.

Add a dollop of the remaining cranberry chutney to each plate.

Finish by drizzling the cranberry sauce over the turkey.